cui_name: MATURITY-ONSET DIABETES OF THE YOUNG, TYPE 7
reasoning: MODY Type 7 is an extremely rare monogenic form of diabetes caused by PAX4 mutations. MODY accounts for 1-5% of diabetes cases globally, and Type 7 is one of the rarest MODY subtypes. Estimated incidence approximately 0.02 per 100k based on rarity among MODY cases. Limited epidemiological data available.
